  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Locally-led and inclusive COVID-19 response in high COVID risk and conflict-affected population in R</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training and technical guidance on inclusive and gender-focused response
Training and technical guidance on advocacy for gender, inclusion and protection
Advocacy for disability-inclusive and gender-focused humanitarian action
Provision of cash for food support to vulnerable households
Distribution of hygiene kits
Distribution of  masks/protective supplies and sanitizers for health workers
Installation of WASH facilities in health centers
Installation of WASH facilities in schools
Development and dissemination of COVID-19 IEC materials for schools and communities
Capacity building and ad hoc support to local partners</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women and men with disabilities are engaged, better protected and included in the response activities and provided suppport                                                                                                                          
Vulnerable households including people with disability, older people and women with specific needs have access to cash to support their basic needs to deal with restrictions/lockdowns and suspension of business activities or to deal with temporary displacements                                                                                           
Education facilities are better prepared to deal with the risk of contamination as they re-open with support of WASH measures in these facilities
  Reduction in risk for populations and minmise the stigma around COVID-19 which allows people to self declare the sympto</narrative>
  </description>
